# Force LF line endings for every text file regardless of the checkout platform's git
# core.autocrlf default. Without this, a Windows CI runner (GitHub Actions windows-latest
# defaults to core.autocrlf=true) checks every source file out with CRLF, and biome's
# formatter -- which always writes LF -- then reports every single file as "differs from
# formatting output" in `biome ci`, failing CI on Windows for files that are otherwise
# correctly formatted (observed: apps/cli/src/main.ts and others, CI run 28652656834).
* text=auto eol=lf

# Windows-only script wrapper Cargo/rustup can generate; harmless to leave CRLF if it
# ever appears, since nothing in this repo formats or lints it.
*.bat text eol=crlf
